1. Ignore Dependencies (The biggest speed killer)

We ignore these because we install them fresh inside the container

node_modules
**/node_modules

2. Ignore Build Artifacts & Caches

These are heavy and platform-specific

**/dist
**/build
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/.cache
coverage

3. Ignore Version Control History

.git can be massive and isn't needed for the build

.git
.gitignore

4. Ignore Environment Files

Security: Don't bake secrets into the image. Pass them at runtime.

.env
.env.*
!.env.example

5. Ignore Logs

npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

6. Ignore IDE/OS Files

.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db